# HEARTBEAT.md - Indie Hackers Agent

## Global Rules
**CLI syntax:** `exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/<command> -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"key":"value"}' 2>&1`
- **evaluate:** `... evaluate --fn 'async () => { ... }' 2>&1` (JS after `--fn`)
- **open/close:** `... open "URL" 2>&1` / `... close 2>&1`
- `evaluate()` for data extraction; `snapshot()` only for clickable refs
- `compact: true`, `interactive: true` on snapshots; scope with `selector: "main"`
- Never `screenshot`; never `args` in evaluate (inline via template literals)
- Never `browser.stop()` or `pkill` -- kills Chrome process
- Max 3 evaluate calls per notification (check + reply + verify)
- Typing = submitting? NO. Always verify text appeared after submit.
- 🚨 Username on IH pages = **"{{handle}}"** (NOT "{{name}}"). Always use "{{handle}}" in page checks.
- 🚨 **NEVER re-insert comment text as a retry strategy.** If submit fails, retry the click ONLY. If verification fails but commentCount increased, treat as success.

## Step Budget (MANDATORY)
- **Target: <30 steps.** Combine remaining work if approaching limit.
- NEVER `exec sleep` — waits go inside evaluate: `() => new Promise(r => setTimeout(() => { r(result); }, 3000))`
- NEVER combine text insert + submit in one evaluate (submit stays disabled until next tick)
- Zero snapshots for engagement. All selectors in BROWSER-*.md — never explore DOM.

**File loading:** BROWSER-core.md is ALWAYS read. Other BROWSER-*.md files are read ON-DEMAND only when needed.

## Decision Tree
```
Heartbeat
  -> Read BROWSER-core.md (selectors/recovery) + limits + schedule
  -> Browser startup (with retry)
  -> Reply check (MANDATORY)
     (🚨 Read BROWSER-replies.md BEFORE extracting notifications)
  -> Execute due tasks
     (Read BROWSER-engage.md for engagement tasks)
  -> Log + Slack
  -> Close browser
  -> HEARTBEAT_OK
```
BOTH reply check AND schedule check are MANDATORY every heartbeat.
🚨 **ALL steps mandatory every heartbeat.** Browser + notifications MUST run even if no tasks are due.
🚨 **NEVER use `sessions_spawn` or sub-sessions.** Execute ALL commands directly — no child sessions.

