## 4. Schedule Check

**Read BROWSER-engage.md first** (for feed extraction, commenting, upvoting).

Read `schedule.json`: `status="pending" AND time<=now`, sort by time.

### browse_and_engage:
```
if daily.comments.current >= limit: mark_done("daily limit reached")
```
**No spacing rule.** Execute tasks back-to-back when due.

1. Browse feed -- extract posts: BROWSER-engage.md S 2. DO NOT navigate individually for stats.
2. Filter in memory: Post Quality Filter from TOOLS.md (2-15 comments, relevant, fresh)
3. 🚨 **MANDATORY: Grep pre-check against tracking file** — for each candidate post, extract its ID:
   - URL has `?post=XXX` → ID = the `XXX` part
   - URL is `/post/slug-hash` → extract BOTH the full `slug-hash` AND just the trailing hash after last `-`
   Then run: `exec grep -qE "^(full_slug_hash|trailing_hash)$" memory/commented_posts.txt && echo "SKIP" || echo "OK"`
   ⚠️ Always STORE the full `slug-hash` in tracking file. The dual check handles legacy short-hash entries.
   If "SKIP" → exclude from candidates (already commented, cheaper than browser navigation)
4. Select 1-2 qualifying posts from remaining candidates
5. For each: navigate → 🚨 **MANDATORY: Read post before commenting** (BROWSER-engage.md S 3 — your comment MUST directly address the returned `title` and `body`) → wait 3s inside first evaluate → **on-page duplicate check** → upvote (S 6, 1 eval) → 🚨 **Apply Comment Quality Rules** (BROWSER-engage.md §A/B/C/D/E/F) → comment (S 5, 3 evals) = **6 evaluates per post**
   - ❌ NEVER use separate `exec sleep 3` for page load wait
   - ✅ Combine page-load wait + duplicate check into upvote evaluate:
     ```javascript
     new Promise(r => setTimeout(() => {
       // Check if we already commented on this post
       var comments = document.querySelectorAll('.comment');
       var alreadyCommented = false;
       comments.forEach(function(c) { if (c.innerText.indexOf('{{handle}}') >= 0) alreadyCommented = true; });
       if (alreadyCommented) return r({ skipped: true, reason: 'already_commented_on_page' });
       // Upvote
       var postUpvote = document.querySelector('.post-liker');
       /* ... upvote logic ... */
       r(result);
     }, 3000))
     ```
   - 🚨 If `skipped: true, reason: 'already_commented_on_page'`: skip comment, append post_id to tracking file, and move on
6. **After each successful comment:** `exec echo "{post_id}" >> memory/commented_posts.txt`
7. After comment: `daily.comments.current++` in limits.json
8. Log: `memory/{today}.md` -> `Type="Comment" | URL | text(100 chars)`
9. 1 comment/heartbeat max. Upvotes unlimited (3-5).
10. `comments_done++`. If `>= max_comments`: mark "done", else "pending"

### Content-Ready Override (publish tasks only)

Before executing any `publish_post` task:

1. Read the file at `config.content_source`
2. Find the first post with `status: pending`
3. Use that content for publishing (extract title and body)
4. After verified publish → update the file: change `status: pending` to `status: published` for that post

### publish_post:

🚨 **Read BROWSER-post.md first** — it has verified selectors. NEVER skip this file and explore DOM manually.

```
if Wednesday: use_weekly_template(TOOLS.md), read_mem(last_7d)
Write post (real data + numbers). Self-review (SOUL.md). Then follow these EXACT steps:
```

**Post creation — 4 evaluates total (steps are in BROWSER-post.md S 7):**
1. Navigate to `https://www.indiehackers.com/new-post` (browser.navigate, NOT snapshot+click)
2. **Evaluate 1:** Dismiss cookie banner + set title
   ```javascript
   fn: `() => {
     var b = document.querySelector('#onetrust-accept-btn-handler');
     if (b) b.click();
     return new Promise(function(resolve) {
       setTimeout(function() {
         var t = document.querySelector('textarea.post-page__title-field');
         if (!t) return resolve({error:'title_field_not_found'});
         t.focus(); t.value = '${postTitle}';
         t.dispatchEvent(new Event('input',{bubbles:true}));
         t.dispatchEvent(new Event('change',{bubbles:true}));
         resolve({success:true, titleLen:t.value.length});
       }, 2000);
     });
   }`
   ```
3. **Evaluate 2:** Set body (plain textarea, NOT TipTap)
   ```javascript
   fn: `() => {
     var b = document.querySelector('textarea.edit-post__body-field');
     if (!b) return {error:'body_field_not_found'};
     b.focus(); b.value = '${postBody}';
     b.dispatchEvent(new Event('input',{bubbles:true}));
     b.dispatchEvent(new Event('change',{bubbles:true}));
     return {success:true, bodyLen:b.value.length};
   }`
   ```
4. **Evaluate 3:** Wait 500ms + click submit
   ```javascript
   fn: `() => new Promise(function(r) { setTimeout(function() {
     var s = document.querySelector('.post-page__submit-button');
     if (!s) return r({error:'submit_not_found'});
     if (s.disabled) return r({error:'submit_disabled'});
     s.click(); r({success:true});
   }, 500); })`
   ```
5. **Evaluate 4:** Wait 4s + verify URL changed
   ```javascript
   fn: `() => new Promise(function(r) { setTimeout(function() {
     r({ url:location.href, isPublished:!location.href.includes('/new-post'), title:document.title });
   }, 4000); })`
   ```
6. If `isPublished: true`: update `weekly.posts.current++`, log `Type="Post Published"`, mark_done()
7. If `isPublished: false`: retry evaluate 3 once. Still false → HEARTBEAT_BLOCKED

Safety net: `Thursday+ AND weekly.posts.current==0` -> publish_now()

❌ **Post creation anti-patterns (Feb 18 violations):**
- ❌ NEVER use snapshot + click on nav links — "Starting Up" tab navigates AWAY from /new-post (cost 2 steps in Feb 18)
- ❌ NEVER search for category selectors — `.category-switch-handler` and `.category-filter-handler` are **cookie consent** elements, NOT post categories (cost 3 steps in Feb 18)
- ❌ NEVER enumerate all buttons with `querySelectorAll('button')` — submit selector is `.post-page__submit-button` (cost 2 steps in Feb 18)
- ❌ NEVER use `innerHTML.slice()` to explore form structure — selectors are in BROWSER-post.md (cost 3 steps in Feb 18)
- ❌ Body is a plain `<textarea>`, NOT TipTap/ProseMirror — use `.value` + input event
- ❌ Group selector shows "You haven't joined any groups" — skip it, post to general feed

